<br>
On a side note, she felt a bit disconcerted about being left behind with all these big, scary mean horse-things, so I needed to give her a nice, big chunk of Elf meat to make her happy again.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I have verified that these command seem to work regardless of range:<br>
/pet follow me<br>
/pet guard here<br>
/pet back off<br>
/pet guard me (synonym for /pet follow me now)<br>
<br>
I seem to have sporadic luck with /pet attack, simply because I think the mob is dead before the pet can get there and so she turns around and goes home.<br>
<br>
Has anybody verified if /pet get lost works from across the zone now? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uiksaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iksaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beastling</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/10/02 7:32:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet commands from across the zone!</span><hr size=1> Yes /pet get lost works across the zone now.<br>
<br>
I love that they did this and hoping it is not just a bug and that they will leave it as is.<br>
<br>
Added with the new nuteral pet codes. You don't know how many time I've told my pet to guard here and then I go walking to a new place forgetting fluffy. Well now I can just tell him to follow and a minute or so later there he is.<br>
<br>
Also get lost os great right now as we can not simply click off our pets. You can click the icon but pet remains, so it's good we can still discard our pets on different sides of the zone. That would so piss me off if I left fluffy on 1 side of the zone and I was on the otehr and I couldn't click him off or just tell him to come over here.<br>
<br>
Fix the icon click off and leave the commands the way there are! <p>____________________<br>
