<br>
No, the pet cannot be dispelled. Not even the icon. Last night I was fighting Fright and the rest of the sub-bosses in Fear and got mass-dispelled several times. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Just to clear things up, &quot;last night&quot; was AFTER the patch that apparently changed the fact with the warder disappearing after the icon was clicked.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure anyone is saying that the warder can be dispelled now.  What people have been saying (including myself) is that it could be dispelled BEFORE this most recent patch, and that &quot;fixing&quot; what people are calling a &quot;bug&quot; could reintroduce that particular vulnerability.  I have positively witnessed my warder being dispelled by Glare Lords in Plane of Fear, but that was before this last patch, or if you prefer, &quot;back in the days when you could click your warder icon to get rid of it.  &quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I've not had it dispelled since, but I also haven't fought any serious dispelling mobs since then.  I'm of the opinion that the warder CANNOT be dispelled now, but I also think that the inability to remove the warder by clicking the icon is directly related to that.<br>
<br>
And maybe the Glare Lord dispel was a bug also, but it seems that now, even if it is a bug, it should no longer have the effect of removing your warder if it happens.  That is a good thing.<br>
<br>
Who knows, maybe VI intended to simply make the warder immune to dispelling, but a side effect of that coding is that you can't click the warder off anymore.  It's not like wizards haven't had issues with their familiars and clicking them off, etc.<br>
<br>
I like it the way it is now for other reasons, too -- like the restored buff slot. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90287 target=_blank><img src=http://www.tchalla.net/BenPortrait.jpg /></a><br>
