<br>
Perhaps it was a bug or there was some other error in my testing, but I know what I saw.<br>
<br>
I also know that the characteristics of wizard familiars have changed several times since release, and it's possible, as I also suggested in earlier posts, that there was a period where VI's tinkering with familiars (which themselves had bugs/vulnerabilites introduced with certain changes) had an effect on warders, which appear to operate under similar rules.  That could explain either the warder being dispelled or the warder NOT being dispelled, depending on what was going on at the time.  And it would explain the disparity between test results if they occured at different times of the evolution of the warder/familiar code.<br>
<br>
All in all, I just don't think it's particularly safe to assert that warders (and their cousins, familiars) cannot, have not, and never will be able to be dispelled, or that it's appropriate to dismiss every report of it having happened (as opposed to vague beliefs that it could happen) as myth or rumor, based primarily on evidence that may not have been obtained under similar conditions (i.e., at equivalent code states). <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90287 target=_blank><img src=http://www.tchalla.net/BenPortrait.jpg /></a><br>
